especially on expected changes that
haven't been considered at design time

30
00:02:10,890 --> 00:02:16,030
will affect them, and potentially make
them more vulnerable to security breaches.

31
00:02:17,450 --> 00:02:19,710
This is true the other way around as well.

32
00:02:21,230 --> 00:02:24,410
Security breaches in
cyber-physical systems

33
00:02:24,410 --> 00:02:27,470
can have serious influence
on their environments.

34
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:35,530
Second, cyber-physical systems can be
composed of a very large number of

35
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:40,539
different devices with different
computing platforms and capabilities.

36
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:47,930
In general, most devices in cyber physical
systems are resource constrained,

37
00:02:47,930 --> 00:02:50,560
meaning that they don't
have much processing,

38
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:55,579
storage, or power capacity to
execute complex operations.

39
00:02:57,350 --> 00:03:01,075
This poses challenges for
applying efficient security

40
00:03:01,075 --> 00:03:06,420
counter-measures that may require
a relatively high amount of resources.

41
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:14,479
Third, cyber-physical systems can
be massively networked systems.

42
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:19,230
They can use various
communication technologies

43
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:23,140
between devices ranging from
simple wired connections

44
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:27,780
to different wireless technologies with
different ranges and characteristics.

45
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:32,640
So they can be highly complex and

46
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:38,700
heterogeneous systems making it
harder to find optimal solutions

47
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:42,670
to ensure secure transmission of
data everywhere in the system.

48
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:48,820
Finally, cyber physical
systems are typically

49
00:03:48,820 --> 00:03:53,839
highly autonomous with embedded
intelligence controlling many operations.

50
00:03:55,250 --> 00:03:59,320
This reduces the need for
manual control and supervision.

51
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:05,890
Which on one hand is an advantage, because
the risk for human error is reduced.

52
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:12,254
On the other hand, the user must be
able to rely on the autonomous system

53
00:04:12,254 --> 00:04:17,076
to be protected against malicious
attacks that aim to secretly alter

54
00:04:17,076 --> 00:04:21,671
the behavior of the system, or
to steal sensitive information.

55
00:04:25,096 --> 00:04:29,939
In general, we can classify
the security requirements of cyber

56
00:04:29,939 --> 00:04:33,353
physical systems into several categories.

57
00:04:35,451 --> 00:04:40,375
In a system, which interacts
with a physical environment,

58
00:04:40,375 --> 00:04:45,020
validity and
accuracy of sensed data is very important.

59
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:49,670
So, proper protection of sensors and

60
00:04:49,670 --> 00:04:53,430
their data is of high
importance in such a system.

61
00:04:56,345 --> 00:05:00,800
Data collected from multiple sensors
needs to be store temporarily.

62
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:09,190
Malicious unauthorized modification of
this stored data results in errors and

63
00:05:09,190 --> 00:05:13,349
is further processing and
can have serious consequences.

64
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:19,765
For this reason, the data while
in storage needs to be protected

65
00:05:19,765 --> 00:05:23,791
against any unauthorized access and
modification.

66
00:05:26,268 --> 00:05:29,363
In some large cyber physical systems,

67
00:05:29,363 --> 00:05:34,331
the data may be collected from
a very large group of sensors over

68
00:05:34,331 --> 00:05:39,600
some time period resulting in a very
large set of data or beak data.

69
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:44,430
The more data you have
the more complex and

70
00:05:44,430 --> 00:05:47,460
difficult it is to
properly secure this data.

71
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:53,640
Many cyber physical systems
are networked and distributed.

72
00:05:55,470 --> 00:06:00,070
Sensitive data is transmitted through
heterogeneous communication channels.

73
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:05,690
Communication security is needed
within a system and between systems.

74
00:06:07,010 --> 00:06:11,416
We will discuss different communication
security protocols in other video

75
