93
00:07:47,260 --> 00:07:52,320
The system needs to be designed to
detect abnormal physical conditions, and

94
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:54,830
act in a safe way in these situations.

95
00:07:56,150 --> 00:08:01,190
Also, the system should always be
protected against physical tampering

96
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,120
whenever possible.

97
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:07,520
Security counter measures
must be considered

98
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:10,120
in the design phase of
a cyber physical system.

99
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:16,530
Security by design means
designing the system as free of

100
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:20,430
vulnerabilities and
resistant against attacks as possible.

101
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:27,420
This can be achieved by continuous
testing and careful design of rigorous

102
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:32,020
authentication solutions and hardware and
software components of the system.

